  m_Name: Level_23_Kaana
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 23
  levelName: Caana
  location: Cayo District, Belize
  levelDescription: "From the Sky Palace, Caracol\u2019s kings ruled above jungle
    and stone.\n\nCaana, meaning \u201CSky Palace\u201D in Maya, is the tallest structure
    at the Caracol archaeological site in western Belize. Rising about 43 meters
    (141 feet), it remains the tallest man-made building in the entire country, towering
    above the jungle canopy.\r\n\r\nBuilt during the Classic Period (c. 600\u2013900
    AD), Caana served as the royal palace and ceremonial heart of Caracol. Its complex
    includes temples, courtyards, and residential chambers, where rulers conducted
    rituals, governance, and daily life. From its summit, the Maya could survey their
    vast city, which at its peak housed tens of thousands of people and rivaled Tikal
    in power.\r\n\r\nToday, climbing Caana offers breathtaking views of the surrounding
    rainforest, connecting visitors to the grandeur and ingenuity of the ancient
    Maya.\r\n"
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 4d30730d713f8254c836f69b3fcdbb55, type: 3}
